**Separation of Concerns**
- Nix manages: interpreter version, system C libraries, shell environment
- uv manages: Python packages, virtual environment, dependency locking
- This separation enables: reproducible builds, cross-platform compatibility, fast rebuilds

**Why Flakes are Mandatory**
- `import <nixpkgs>` is impure (non-reproducible, breaks on different machines)
- Flakes pin all inputs (nixpkgs version, dependencies) via `flake.lock`
- Multi-system support (`systems = [...]`) is first-class in flakes

**Why uv (not pip/poetry)**
- Fastest Python package manager (written in Rust)
- Native lockfile support (uv.lock tracks transitive dependencies)
- Compatible with standard `pyproject.toml` (no vendor lock-in)
